OL,7,FSome people with ulcerative colitis
OL,8,Fmay go for weeks or months with very
OL,9,Fmild symptoms, or none at all
OL,10,F(remission), followed by flare-ups and
OL,11,Frelapses, according to the NHS website.
OL,13,FTreatment options include
OL,14,Fcorticosteroids, immunosuppressants
OL,15,Fand surgery.
OL,17,FCharity Crohn's And Colitis UK says
OL,18,Fthere are more than 300,000 people in
OL,19,Fthe UK living with colitis.JThe main
OL,20,Fsymptoms of ulcerative colitis are:
